section.section:
The provisions of this section apply to:
Licensed premises that are operated by selling alcoholic beverages directly to a customer from a bar or service bar on the premises;
Premises licensed for off sale;
In Montgomery County, a holder of a caterer's license issued under § 6-706.1 of this article; and
In Baltimore City, an establishment covered under § 20-102(a) of this article.

This section does not apply to:
Temporary alcoholic beverages licenses issued under § 7-101 of this article;
A Class E (on-sale) steamboat alcoholic beverages license;
A Class F (on-sale) railroad alcoholic beverages license; or
A Class G (on-sale) aircraft alcoholic beverages license.
